wikipedia_page.main: Albert John Collins (16 January 1899 – 1 December 1969) was an English footballer who played professionally for clubs including Millwall and Gillingham. He made 170 Football League appearances for the latter club. On leaving Gillingham he went into non-League football, first with Tunbridge Wells Rangers and finally with Canterbury Waverley.
